Industry News and Updates

Ohio Attorney General Debt Collection 5/20/2019 Read more
The Ohio Attorney General’s office will attempt to collect an EMS Agency’s unpaid transport bills that are the patient’s responsibility.; after Medicount has exhausted all means of payment recovery. If you are interested in using this service, contact the Ohio Attorney General Collection Enforcement Agency at (614) 466-4510. You can access the required forms and some basic information about the program on the Ohio Attorney General’s webpage
Analyzing Non Emergency Facility Transport Costs 11/12/2018 Read more
Analyzing Your Transport Costs for Non-Emergency Transport Agreements with Facilities If your Ambulance Agency regularly transports patients from a specific facility (Hospitals, SNF’s – Skilled Nursing Facilities, Hospice Facilities), it may be in your best interest to enter into an agreement with the referring facility for Insurance Non-Covered Services. Agreements between the facility and your Ambulance Agency greatly increase the efficiency of the billing process and collection of revenue (ie. Speeds up payments).
